On 17 June 2020, Samoa announces that it will now allow travel between Samoa and American Samoa on a Cabinet approved boat with restrictions. 
(i) the person travelling to Samoa has resided in American Samoa for more than 14 days;
(ii) the person upon arrival is not subject to quarantine.

